English.Text: Stress and inexperience slow your doctor down. With trembling fingers, he slowly pulls a piece of wood out of the man's abdomen. But there are many left to go, and the menacing creaks above their head make the young doctor shudder even more violently. Before long, another pumpkin-shaped grenade blasts both patient and doctor with wooden shrapnel. The latter manages to cover most of it with his forearms, but the patient's now coughing up blood.
